The paper focuses on link prediction in bipartite networks using a Linear-Graph Autoencoder (LGAE) and proposes a method to improve its performance by considering 2-hop paths. This involves learning vector space representations of nodes based on the adjacency matrix of the graph. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on both synthetic and real-world datasets. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper primarily deals with a machine learning model. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound) as the paper deals with network analysis and graph theory. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible sub-categories as the paper deals with algorithms and machine learning techniques.
